Date: Mon 8 Sep 2003
From: Richard Gould <rgould@avdha.nshealth.ca>

A Comment on the Validity of SARS Diagnostic Tests
--------------------------------------------------
Watchfulness and caution are important. However, is too much weight being
placed on the lab tests?
Do we have any good idea of the sensitivity and specificity of these
tests? Perhaps they may be helpful in an outbreak. But what is the
positive predictive value for a sporadic case with no epidemiological link
to other cases and with nonspecific symptoms that may be similar to many
other viruses? Turning the health care system upside down for a cold isn't
appropriate either.
--
Richard Gould MD MHSc FRCPC
Medical Officer of Health
District Health Authorities 1 - 3
23 Earnscliffe Ave.
Wolfville, Nova Scotia, B4P 1X4
<rgould@avdha.nshealth.ca>
